Underdeveloped kidney-Qi in children can affect bone development.
Sores and ulcers with initial redness, swelling, heat and pain mostly belong to Yang syndrome.
Chronic sores and ulcers with dull dark color mostly belong to Yin syndrome.
Foul-smelling pus often indicates exuberance of pathogenic toxins.
