A state of vitality often reflects that healthy Qi has not declined.
Reduced vitality often indicates insufficiency of healthy Qi.
Loss of vitality often indicates decline of essence and Qi.
False vitality often indicates impending separation of Yin and Yang.
A greenish complexion is often related to cold syndrome or blood stasis.
A reddish complexion is often related to heat syndrome.
A yellow complexion is often related to spleen deficiency or dampness syndrome.
A pale complexion is often related to deficiency syndrome or cold syndrome.
A dark complexion is often related to kidney deficiency or water-fluid retention.
Obesity is often related to internal exuberance of phlegm-dampness.
Emaciation is often related to insufficiency of Yin and blood.
Preference for quietness and reluctance to move often indicate Yang-Qi insufficiency.
Restlessness often indicates heat disturbing the mind.
