A heavy turbid voice often indicates obstruction by phlegm-dampness.
Rapid breathing is often related to upward reversal of lung-Qi.
A clear ringing cough often indicates wind-cold invading the lungs.
A muffled cough often indicates phlegm-dampness obstructing the lungs.
Frequent belching is often related to upward reversal of stomach-Qi.
Repeated hiccup often indicates upward reversal of stomach-Qi.
Vomiting sour and putrid matter often indicates food accumulation retained in the stomach.
Marked halitosis is often related to stomach heat or food accumulation.
Preference for hot drinks often indicates cold syndrome.
Preference for cold drinks often indicates heat syndrome.
